    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Geth already ships (though not yet enabled by default) a superset of the Parity snapshot (https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/pull/20152) that can also be used for EVM acceleration and Merkle proven state syncs (https://github.com/ethereum/devp2p/pull/145) .It also seems to perform crazy well (https://twitter.com/peter_szilagyi/status/1264801013174845442).\r\n\r\nAll in all I don't think there's any value for us to support Parity's \"legacy\" snapshot format. It would just be code we'd need to maintain for no benefit. ",
